The run mode for a custom run test specified in Run.mode().

Run

  • Enum Constant Summary

    Enum Constants
    Enum Constant
    Description
    NORMAL
    Default mode: First warm up the run method (if a warm-up is done), then compile the associated Test method and finally invoke the run method once more.
    STANDALONE
    Standalone mode: There is no warm-up and no compilation done by the framework.

  • Enum Constant Details

    • NORMAL

      public static final RunMode NORMAL
      Default mode: First warm up the run method (if a warm-up is done), then compile the associated Test method and finally invoke the run method once more.

    • STANDALONE

      public static final RunMode STANDALONE
      Standalone mode: There is no warm-up and no compilation done by the framework. The run method is responsible to trigger the compilation(s), especially in regard of possible IR annotations at the associated Test method.
